# Authentication Standards

Follow the canonical standard: **`.ai/standards/devise-auth.md`**

Key rules:
- Enable only the Devise modules you need; use `confirmable` and `lockable`
- Web: secure/httponly/samesite cookies; APIs: token strategy (e.g. devise-jwt), not the session cookie
- Add 2FA for admin and privileged roles
- Rate-limit login, password reset, and confirmation endpoints (Rack::Attack)
- Authenticate is not authorize — always authorize server-side
- Never store tokens or reset secrets in plain text or logs

Agent: `.ai/agents/backend-rails-developer.yaml`, `.ai/agents/security-reviewer.yaml`  
Related: `.ai/standards/security.md`
